<HEADLINE>
<P>
MISSILE TEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I sure hope that all the reader's of the Los Angeles Times enjoyed that 
spectacular front-page photo (March 22) of the fizzled Trident 2 missile doing 
cartwheels off the coast of Cape Canaveral. 
</P>
<P>
A magnificent sight to behold as our taxes to the tune of $23.7 million went up 
in smoke. It's no wonder the folks at the IRS find it hard to deal with the 
natives in this country on April 15th! 
</P>
<P>
ARTHUR J. BREZAE 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth 
</P>
</TEXT>
