<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEIL PITCHES HART TO 1-0 SOFTBALL VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hart High won a battle of windmill pitchers as junior right-hander Kym Weil 
outdueled Cathy Lewis of Saugus to give Hart a 1-0 nonleague victory Tuesday 
night at Santa Clarita Park. 
</P>
<P>
Weil (12-1), who has not allowed an earned run this season, struck out 11 and 
pitched a two-hitter. Lewis (7-6), a senior left-hander, pitched a five-hitter 
and struck out 10. 
</P>
<P>
Jamie Dean scored from third base in the sixth for Hart (13-1) on a throwing 
error by Saugus catcher Heather Lonsberry. 
</P>
