<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATWATCH: HART ROLLS ALONG DESPITE LOSS OF EDWARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Despite the fact that All-Southern Section selection Jason Edwards has yet to 
pitch, Hart High (11-1) is ranked fourth in the nation by USA Today, thanks in 
part to the contributions of two underclassmen. Junior left-hander Andrew 
Lorraine is 4-0 with a 1.06 earned-run average and sophomore right-hander Keith 
Halcovich is 3-1 with a 1.75 ERA. The staff ERA is 1.78. 
</P>
<P>
Edwards, a Times All-Valley pick last season with an 11-0 record, has been 
relegated to the role of designated-hitter this season because of an inflamed 
rotator cuff in his right shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
Hitting: Hart has seven players batting over .300, the team batting average is 
.349 and the team on-base percentage is .449. Catcher Casey Burrill, who has 
orally commited to USC, is batting .560 with three home runs and three doubles. 
Lance Migita, who has a team-high eight doubles, is hitting .467. David Toledo 
is batting .432 and Robby Davis is at .421. 
</P>
<P>
Streaks: Chatsworth (9-2) has won 21 consecutive West Valley League baseball 
games since a 4-1 loss to Canoga Park in 1987. With a two-game sweep of Taft 
last week, Chatsworth has won 25 games in a row over the Toreadors, a streak 
that began in 1981. 
</P>
<P>
Stolen bases: Darrell Davis of Saugus set a school record last week with his 
43rd career stolen base and has 14 of the team's 35 steals. Ironically, the 
Centurions have been caught stealing only three times all season -- and Davis 
was the man each time. 
</P>
<P>
San Fernando's Jess Romero has seven stolen bases in eight attempts and Pat 
Bryant of Cleveland has six steals in seven tries. . . . Westlake's Tim Falsken 
has 13 stolen bases, one shy of the single-season school record. 
</P>
<P>
Pitching: Westlake pitchers Mike Eby, John Brookman and Scott Lerner have 
walked only 18 batters in 74 1/3 innings. 
</P>
<P>
Crespi's Pat Bennett, after pitching 30 1/3 innings with an 0.00 ERA, 
surrendered his first earned run in a 12-11 loss to El Segundo on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
