<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Carl Karcher Enterprises: The Anaheim-based fast-food chain reported that 
profits jumped 30% to $21 million in fiscal 1989. Sales totaled $446 million, 
an increase of 21% over a year ago. The company attributed the strong 
performance to the success of new menu items, a major remodeling program and a 
"back-to-basics" strategy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
