<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: NATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
William F. Glavin, a Xerox vice chairman and a member of the company's 
four-member corporate office, will take early retirement June 1 to accept the 
presidency of Babson College in Wellesley, Mass. Glavin, 57, also will not 
stand for reelection to the board of directors of Xerox at the company's annual 
meeting in May. He will not be replaced either as vice chairman or as a member 
of the corporate office. 
</P>
<P>
Glavin will become head of Babson, an independent, coeducational business 
school, July 1. 
</P>
