<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: NATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Katharine Graham, chairman of the Washington Post Co., has accepted an 
invitation to become an independent trustee of Reuters Founders Share Co. The 
company, which operates the Reuters news agency, will have 14 trustees as of 
May 2, when Graham's appointment becomes effective. Ten of the trustees are 
appointed by newspaper associations in Britain, Australia and New Zealand, and 
the other four are independent. 
</P>
