<P>
Former Arizona Gov. Evan Mecham -- impeached and removed from office a year ago 
-- said he will run again in 1990. "I committed no impeachable offense," the 
Republican said at an evening rally at a hotel in Phoenix. The audience of 
about 400 gave a standing ovation to Mecham and his wife, Florence, when they 
arrived. The 64-year-old former auto dealer, elected in 1986 on his fifth try 
for governor, was convicted by the Arizona Senate and removed April 4, 1988, on 
charges he misused funds and obstructed justice. Earlier in the day, Mecham 
said he had filed papers with the Senate asking it to reconsider the votes by 
which it impeached and ousted him. Senate leaders said they doubted lawmakers 
would grant the motion. 
