<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: ARIZONA ACTS AGAINST PLAYERS IN ASSAULT CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three of the four Arizona freshman football players arrested last month in 
connection with a series of campus assaults have been suspended from the school 
for two years and a fourth has been put on probation, the university's dean of 
students said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Rosalind E. Andreas said that the three players must decide this week whether 
to accept or appeal the sanctions. She would not name the suspended students, 
but four players -- offensive lineman Michael Bundy, defensive back Samuel 
Edwards, quarterback Sean Hutson and walk-on wide receiver Jeffrey King -- were 
arrested March 9 and charged with misdemeanor assaults. 
</P>
<P>
The players were accused of a series of random attacks in which 11 people were 
beaten during a two-hour period. Several were treated at hospitals for bruises 
and black eyes, and at least one was treated for a broken nose, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
