<P>
DEAD BABY'S MOTHER MAY BE CHARGED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An unidentified mother whose baby boy died at San Dimas Community Hospital one 
hour after birth may face criminal charges, depending on the outcome of an 
autopsy and other tests. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department homicide detectives are investigating 
whether the infant -- born three months prematurely Monday -- may have died as 
a result of the mother's cocaine habit. 
</P>
<P>
Charges against such mothers are rarely filed, although Los Angeles County 
coroner's spokesman Bob Dambacher said last year that more than 40 infant 
deaths were ruled "accidental, due to maternal drug abuse," and more than 30 as 
"natural, but with a history of maternal drug abuse." 
</P>
</TEXT>
