<HEADLINE>
<P>
JUDGE REFUSES TO STOP RINGING OF CHURCH BELL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NORTHAMPTON, Mass. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A small-town church in rural Hatfield has rung up a first-round victory in its 
battle of the bell. 
</P>
<P>
A judge has refused to silence the bell at the Hatfield Congregational Church, 
ruling that a couple next door who claim the ringing has left them with 
sleepless nights will have to prove their case at trial, a spokeswoman said 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Hampshire Superior Court Judge John Murphy Jr. refused to grant a preliminary 
injunction that would have prevented the bell from tolling between 9 p.m. and 7 
a.m. each day, a court spokeswoman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
