<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEDDINGS CAN INJURE PEOPLE, OFFICIALS DECIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OKLAHOMA CITY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It's just not safe anymore to get married, and Oklahoma County commissioners 
are doing something about it. 
</P>
<P>
The commissioners voted Monday to ban a traditional wedding practice -- the 
throwing of such things as rice and confetti -- in the vicinity of the county 
courthouse. 
</P>
<P>
Commissioner F. G. Buchanan said the policy was adopted as a safety measure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
