one run, 3-2. Villa Park tied the score in the fifth on an error. Todd Blyleven 
(2-2) pitched to one batter in the seventh to earn the victory. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon 8, Santa Ana Valley 5 -- The Comanches (7-2, 2-2) scored four runs in 
the bottom of the sixth for an 8-3 lead. Mike Casagranda relieved winning 
pitcher Marty Little and got the final two outs to earn the save. Canyon's Dan 
Puskas went three for three, scoring three runs. 
</P>
<P>
In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
