<HEADLINE>
<P>
ICN OF COSTA MESA POSTS JUMP IN INCOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ICN Biomedicals Inc. of Costa Mesa posted a 43% increase in first-quarter net 
income, to $942,000 from $661,000 for the comparable period a year ago. The 
first-quarter 1989 figure included a $273,000 gain from repurchase of debt. 
Revenue for the 3 months ended Feb. 28, 1989, rose 14%, to $12.9 million from 
$11.4 million. The company produces and markets research chemicals and related 
products, including reagents, immunochemicals and instruments for diagnostic 
testing in clinical laboratories. 
</P>
