<P>
PASADENA GIRL, 2, SHOT TO DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 2-year-old Pasadena girl was shot and killed when the station wagon in which 
she was riding with her grandmother and several other children was fired upon 
Tuesday evening in Rubidoux, authorities said today. They said the motive was 
unclear. 
</P>
<P>
Karina Cherise Williams was pronounced dead at Riverside Community Hospital 
shortly after the 8:15 p.m. shooting, said Lt. Nick Padilla of the Riverside 
County Sheriff's Department. He said several shots were fired at two vehicles 
carrying eight adults and four children in the same party. The attack occurred 
less than a block from a home where the girl and her grandmother had visited 
relatives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
