<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
CHASE ENDS IN SUSPECT'S DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A burglary suspect was shot to death by Inglewood police on the Santa Monica 
Freeway this morning after a two-hour, 100-mile chase through three counties at 
speeds of up to 100 m.p.h., officers reported. 
</P>
<P>
Officers said they shot Javier Salvador Arreola, 23, after finally stopping him 
at 2:16 a.m. on the eastbound lanes near La Brea Avenue because he appeared to 
be rummaging for a weapon. They said they found "a substantial amount" of 
cocaine in his van, but it was not immediately determined whether he had a 
weapon. Officers said the pursuit began after Arreola was seen circling a 
construction site. 
</P>
<P>
Traffic on the freeway was blocked for more than four hours by the police 
investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
