NATION; 
</P>
<P>
GINGRICH NAMES 2 DEPUTY WHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Reps. Robert S. Walker of Pennsylvania and Steve Gunderson of Wisconsin were 
appointed today as chief deputy whips for the House Republicans. 
</P>
<P>
They were chosen by Rep. Newt Gingrich of Georgia, the new Republican whip. 
</P>
<P>
Gingrich selected activist, philosophically different congressmen. Walker, from 
the conservative wing, is known for maneuvers on the House floor aimed at 
foiling Democratic initiatives. Gunderson is a leader among more moderate 
Republicans who have tried to push alternatives to Democratic legislation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
