<HEADLINE>
<P>
CADUFF WINS MEN'S DOWNHILL RACE IN JAPAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Daniel Caduff beat fellow Swiss skier Peter Mueller by 0.01 seconds to win the 
men's downhill race today in the Lark Sports World International Grand Prix in 
north-central Japan. 
</P>
<P>
Austria's Anita Wachter, who won the women's downhill in the Japan Alpine Ski 
Championships at the same Shiga Kogen ski course Tuesday, captured the women's 
crown again today with a time of 1:43.27. 
</P>
<P>
Caduff, 21, flashed down the 8,356-foot course in one minute, 37.36 seconds, 
beating 31-year-old Mueller, now ranked sixth by the International Ski 
Federation. Mueller finished in 1:37.37. 
</P>
</TEXT>
