<P>
DELANY NAMED TO HEAD BIG TEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
James E. Delany was named today to succeed Wayne Duke as commissioner of the 
Big Ten athletic conference. 
</P>
<P>
Delany was introduced at a news conference late this morning. He had been 
considered the leading candidate to succeed Duke, who announced his retirement 
earlier this year. 
</P>
<P>
Delany, 41, a native of South Orange, N.J., has served as commissioner of the 
Ohio Valley Conference since July, 1979. Earlier, he worked in the NCAA rules 
enforcement division and as an associate attorney general in North Carolina's 
state Justice Department. 
</P>
